  "text": "The first condition is that the ratio between α h and β h is common over all agents. Notice that this condition still allows for heterogenous, truly recursive utility functions since α's and β's need not be common. The second condition is the common prior assumption. [CITATION_1] Note that there is no restriction on subjective discount factors, thus in particular they can be heterogeneous.",
